  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@MorenoDiDomenico helper.setQueryParameter resets the page to 0. In order to prevent you can reassign the current page value or you can do the following:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearchFunction: function(h) {\r\n    if (search.helper.hasRefinements('cat_color')) {\r\n      search.helper.setState(search.helper.state.setQueryParameter('distinct', true));\r\n    } else {\r\n      search.helper.setState(search.helper.state.setQueryParameter('distinct', false));\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    h.search();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can do this because setState does not impact the pagination.",
    "created_at": "2017-03-20T17:15:37Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2044#issuecomment-287831001",
